'''Jacob Lynn "Jake" Pavelka''' (born January 27, 1978) is an [[United States|American]] pilot who appeared on six [[reality TV]] programs, most notably ''[[The Bachelor (US TV series)|The Bachelor]]''.
== Early life and career == Pavelka was born in [[Dallas, Texas]] to Sallie Lanell ([[née]] Mack) and James Lynn Pavelka. He is the middle child of three sons. His brothers, Jason and Matthew, are both married. He has two nephews. Pavelka grew up in [[Denton, Texas]] and he started taking flying lessons when he was twelve. He eventually worked as a pilot for [[Atlantic Southeast Airlines]], and under the name of Jake Landrum, acted in several television commercials and programs produced in the Dallas area.<ref name=TVG>{{cite news | author = | title =Jake Pavelka Biography | publisher =TV Guide Online | date = | url =http://www.tvguide.com/celebrities/jake-pavelka/bio/298929 | accessdate=2009-03-30}}</ref> Pavelka is a cousin of fitness model, television presenter, actor and personal trainer [[Jessie Pavelka]]. Pavelka participates in [[triathlons]] and has been active in fitness throughout his life.
== Reality television ==
Pavelka first appeared as a contestant in 2009, in the fifth season of the [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]] reality show ''[[The Bachelorette]]''. He was eliminated from the competition, but was brought back by the network to star in the [[The Bachelor (season 14)|14th season of its series ''The Bachelor'']] in 2010. The program’s run ended with Pavelka proposing marriage to contestant [[Vienna Girardi]] in the March 2010 finale.<ref name=TVG /> The couple split up in June 2010.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Jake-Vienna-Split-1019818.aspx|title=The Bachelor's Jake Pavelka and Vienna Girardi Split|publisher=TVGuide.com}}</ref>
Following the end of ''The Bachelor'', Pavelka was named as one of the celebrity contestants for the tenth season of ''[[Dancing with the Stars (U.S. season 10)|Dancing with the Stars]]''.<ref>{{cite news | author =Joyce Eng | title =Dancing’s Jake Pavelka: I Feel Dumb Every Day in Rehearsal | publisher =Seattle Post-Intelligencer | date =March 25, 2010 | url =http://www.seattlepi.com/tvguide/417403_dancing25.html| accessdate=2010-03-30}} {{Dead link|date=October 2010|bot=H3llBot}}</ref> He and his partner [[Chelsie Hightower]] were the fifth to be eliminated, in April 2010. In July 2011, Pavelka was a contestant on the second season of ''[[Bachelor Pad]]''.<ref>{{cite web|last=Bierly |first=Mandi |url=http://insidetv.ew.com/2011/06/13/bachelor-pad-cast-season-2/ |title=Official 'Bachelor Pad' cast revealed - EXCLUSIVE &#124; Inside TV &#124; EW.com |publisher=Insidetv.ew.com |date=2011-06-13 |accessdate=2012-07-26}}</ref> He was also a contestant on [[VH1]]'s 2011 reality series ''[[Famous Food]]'', and appeared on a September 2011 episode of [[The CW]]'s reality show ''[[H8R]]''. In 2014, he was a contestant on ''Rachael vs. Guy: Celebrity Cook-Off.''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foodnetwork.com/rachael-vs-guy-celebrity-cook-off/index.html|title=Rachael vs. Guy: Celebrity Cook-Off|publisher=|accessdate=8 August 2018}}</ref> On May 23, 2016, he appeared as a surprise guest on the Bachelorette with [[JoJo Fletcher]].
== Other work== In June 2010, Pavelka was scheduled to guest-star on an episode of ''[[Drop Dead Diva]]'' as Toby Devlin, contestant on a fictional reality dating show.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvguide.com/News/Jake-Pavelka-Diva-1019583.aspx|title=Jake Pavelka to Play a Bachelor on Drop Dead Diva|publisher=TVGuide.com}}</ref> On January 14, 2011, Pavelka guest-starred on ''[[The Bold and the Beautiful]]''.<ref>{{cite web|url= http://www.tvguide.com/News/Bachelors-Jake-Pavelka-1025792.aspx|title= The Bachelor's Jake Pavelka to Guest-Star on The Bold and the Beautiful|publisher=TVGuide.com|accessdate=November 19, 2010}}</ref>
From February to March 2012, Pavelka was a celebrity guest host at the [[Chippendales]] show in [[Las Vegas Strip|Las Vegas]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.eonline.com/news/which_hunky_bachelor_star_joining/292723 |title=Which Hunky Bachelor Star Is Joining Chippendales |publisher=E! Online |date=2012-02-08 |accessdate=2012-07-26}}</ref>
